    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-02-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-02-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="455"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d455">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862i.73/41</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Netherlands Chargé</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">De Beaufort</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-02-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 25, 1922</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 540</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have not failed to communicate to my Government
                    the text of the memorandum containing a tentative draft of an arrangement <pb
                        facs="0861" n="765" xml:id="pg_765"/> between the Five Powers regarding the
                    disposal of the Yap Cables formerly owned by the Netherland German Telegraph
                    Company which memorandum was handed to me by the State Department in January
                        last.<note n="10" xml:id="d455fn10">Memorandum not printed; it consisted of
                        the text of the draft of arrangement quoted in the Under Secretary’s
                        memorandum of Mar. 25, 1922, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Referring to paragraph three of this memorandum and acting upon instructions
                    received from my Government, I have now the honor to inform the United States
                    Government that the Netherland Government accepts the Yap–Menado Cable under the
                    arrangement as set forth in the memorandum, copy of which is enclosed
                    herewith.</p>
                <p>Please accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. de Beaufort</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
